# Cursor Rules
# This file contains rules for the Cursor AI assistant.

# Communication Language
# - The assistant MUST communicate with the user in Russian (Русский язык).

# Project Context
# - This is a sandbox project for prototyping UI components with ImGui.
# - The project uses CMake for build configuration.
# - The project uses C++20 standard.
# - The build directory is `_build`.

# Coding Style
# - Use C++ for backend/native code.

# Documentation
# - Add comments for complex logic.

# Directory Structure
# - Place third-party libraries in `thirdparty/`.
#   - Current third-party libs: `imgui`, `glfw`, `spdlog`, `catch2`, `nlohmann_json`, `immer`, `magic_enum`.
# - Place project source code in:
#   - `src/apps/` for applications.
#   - `src/libs/` for shared libraries.

# Build Instructions
# - Use `build_vs.bat` to generate and build the project for Visual Studio.
# - CMake build output goes to `_build/`.
# - Executables are located in `_build/bin/Debug/` (or Release).
# - Third-party libraries (like ImGui) are linked as static libraries.

# Dependencies
# - ImGui is located in `thirdparty/imgui`. It includes GLFW and OpenGL3 backends.
# - GLFW is located in `thirdparty/glfw`.
